article.description: — Morgan Safford had 14 points to lead five Wofford players in double figures as the Terriers easily beat Western Carolina 80-56 on Saturday.
article.headline: Safford, Godwin lead Wofford over W. Carolina 80-56
article.linkText: Safford, Godwin lead Wofford over W. Carolina 80-56
article.story: CULLOWHEE, N.C. -- — Morgan Safford had 14 points to lead five Wofford players in double figures as the Terriers easily beat Western Carolina 80-56 on Saturday. Sam Godwin added 12 points for the Terriers and Messiah Jones, Tray Hollowell and Storm Murphy each scored 11. Wofford (14-8, 11-5 Southern Conference) distributed a season-high 23 assists on 33-made field goals. Cory Hightower scored a career-high 26 points for the Catamounts (9-14, 2-12) and Sin’Cere McMahon added 13 points. The Terriers also beat Western Carolina 91-78 on Jan. 23. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
